{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Etymology===
[[bombardier]] + [[beetle]]

===Noun===
'''bombardier beetle''' (''plural:'' '''bombardier beetles''')

#{{entomology}} A beetle whose defence mechanism enables it to eject a hot aqueous mixture of chemicals at predators. They come from a number of subfamilies: Carabinae (e.g., ''Brachinus crepitans''), Metriinae (e.g., ''Stenaptinus insignis'') and Paussinae (e.g., ''Goniotropis nicaraguensis'').

